<blockquote>

<p><b>Rules of Conduct</b></p>

<p>1. Posts containing excessive vulgarity may be edited or removed. Although we have no desire to reduce our users option to use a curse word to prove a point, we will remove any post made with no point other than to curse. Vulgarity is defined to be anything a normal individual would find offensive, and may vary slightly from moderator to moderator. New threads with vulgar or sexually explicit subject lines or posted content will be subject to removal.*</p>

<p>2. Posts containing sexually explicit content (whether it is graphics or text), Hard or softcore graphical or photographic images, links to soft or hardcore pornographic websites or sites with questionable content may be removed and the offending user may be banned.*</p>

<p>3. EverLore is a spam-free community. Advertisements, chain letters, pyramid schemes, solicitations, repeated bumping of old threads for no reason, and posts that are designed in a way to damage or inhibit the operation of the system or the enjoyment of other posters may be removed.*</p>

<p>4. Mild, intelligent flaming is allowable, however personal attacks on another poster or a group of posters up to and including threats of physical harm, posts designed to bait others into argument (commonly known as "trolling"), and posts created for the sole purpose of insulting another poster or group of posters, including EverLore Moderators and Staff, may be removed. * Personal attacks may include, but are not limited to, epithets/slurs targeting a person’s race, sexual orientation, religion, social status, or intelligence level. Images posted that contain symbols that are generally percieved to be symbols of hate or intolerance may be removed and a warning issued. Lastly, images or signatures made to slander any staff member or website of the RPGLore Network will be removed and a warning issued.</p>

<p>5. The Off-Topic forum will be monitored in the same way as all other forums for content. This forum is designed to discuss topics not related to EverQuest or EverLore. All posts within it are subject to the same moderation as any other forum on EverLore. Any posts within Off-Topic violating the Forum Rules may be removed. Any posts not directly related to EverQuest or EverLore posted in any forum may be moved to the Off-Topic forum at the discretion of the Moderators.
Further, Off-Topic threads posted in other forums may be deleted or moved by Moderators. Users are asked to ensure that their threads are placed in the proper forums for the topic of discussion.</p>

<p>6. Posters are required to limit the size of images in their signatures to be no larger than 400x300 pixels. Also, please restrict the memory size of the images as well, remember what seems okay to you on cable/dsl maybe an extremely large file to someone on a dial up.</p>

<p>7. Any post where users advertise the use of or, provide links to ad removal software will be deleted. If a user continues to post links to ad removal software their user accounts and IP's will be banned.</p>

<p>8. The use of coding is not allowed within posts. Posts with code included are subject to removal. Code includes, but isn’t limited to Java, javascript, flash and shockwave. HTML coding is excepted from this clause, but please see rule #3 for how this is to be moderated.</p>

<p>9. The impersonation of another person on the boards will be grounds for a warning and or a temporary banning depending on the severity of the case. This includes use of other clan/guild images or tags in the attempt to discredit them.</p>

<p>10. Personal threats or repeated verbal abuse to site staff over any method of communcation such as ICQ or email may result in suspension and or banning the offender's account.</p>

